== Overview ==

Dragon Quest III for SNES features over 100 unique monsters across the overworld and dungeons. This page documents monster statistics and behaviors.

== Monster Data Structure ==

Each monster entry is 32 bytes:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Offset !! Size !! Description
|-
| $00-$01 || 2 || HP
|-
| $02-$03 || 2 || MP
|-
| $04 || 1 || Attack
|-
| $05 || 1 || Defense
|-
| $06 || 1 || Agility
|-
| $07 || 1 || Intelligence
|-
| $08-$09 || 2 || Experience
|-
| $0A-$0B || 2 || Gold
|-
| $0C || 1 || Drop item ID
|-
| $0D || 1 || Drop rate
|-
| $0E || 1 || Elemental resistance
|-
| $0F || 1 || Status resistance
|-
| $10-$1F || 16 || AI patterns, abilities
|}

